over a million views this month

06:24.880 --> 06:26.359
and my--

06:26.560 --> 06:28.790
--own advertisers.

06:29.000 --> 06:30.479
That's my girl!

06:30.680 --> 06:32.796
Not just another pretty face.

06:37.200 --> 06:42.115
Miss Shelley, I've got something special for you today.

06:42.920 --> 06:45.639
Think you're gonna like it.

06:45.880 --> 06:48.633
Oh my, chicken!

06:48.880 --> 06:53.317
I don't know when was the last time I had chicken.

06:53.840 --> 06:58.118
That would be yesterday, for lunch and dinner.

06:58.320 --> 07:00.709
Are you serious?

07:00.920 --> 07:04.549
I don't think that she should
have the same thing every--

07:05.080 --> 07:08.755
You think of anything else gonna make her that happy?

07:19.560 --> 07:22.358
Is it okay if I help?

07:22.560 --> 07:26.394
Oh, alright, alright.

07:28.600 --> 07:31.433
You're new here, aren't you?

07:31.640 --> 07:33.073
It's me, Mom.

07:33.280 --> 07:36.078
Mina, your daughter.

07:39.760 --> 07:43.036
I'm sorry, I don't--

07:43.240 --> 07:46.869
It's okay, it's okay.

07:49.920 --> 07:54.869
I don't see a ring.

07:55.080 --> 07:57.799
It's complicated.

08:24.920 --> 08:28.276
I am Professor Radisson and this is Philosophy 150,

08:28.520 --> 08:31.193
Introduction to Philosophical Thought.

08:31.440 --> 08:33.874
If either of those facts is news to you,

08:34.080 --> 08:38.517
then now would be your turn to leave.

08:42.039 --> 08:43.438
I understand some of you are here

08:43.640 --> 08:47.918
to satisfy your Liberal Arts elective requirements.

08:48.120 --> 08:50.111
If you're looking for an easy grade without much work,

08:50.320 --> 08:53.312
well, then now would be your turn to leave.

08:53.520 --> 08:55.272
See, you've now enrolled at a university.

08:55.480 --> 08:58.916
You'll be expected to produce
university-level work.

08:59.120 --> 09:02.317
Pfft, I'm out.

09:07.400 --> 09:09.755
There's always one.

09:09.960 --> 09:12.679
Michel Foucault, Bertrand Russel,

09:12.880 --> 09:15.713
Ludwig Feuerbach, Bertolt Brecht,

09:15.920 --> 09:18.229
Friedrich Nietzsche, Ayn Rand, George Santayana,

09:18.440 --> 09:20.795
Democritus, Denis Diderot, David Hume,

09:21.000 --> 09:23.673
John Stuart Mill, Albert Camus, Richard Dawkins,

09:23.880 --> 09:26.599
Sigmund Freud, Noam Chomsky.

09:26.800 --> 09:28.756
The list goes on.

09:29.000 --> 09:33.073
Philosophers, poets, scientists, authors,

09:33.280 --> 09:37.353
towering intellects, all of them.

09:37.560 --> 09:43.715
But what do they all have in common?

09:44.800 --> 09:46.199
Yes?

09:46.400 --> 09:48.277
They're all dead.

09:48.520 --> 09:51.080
Well, that would be incorrect.

09:51.280 --> 09:54.955
Mr. Dawkins and Mr. Chomsky are
still very much alive, Mister--

09:55.160 --> 09:58.789
G-dog Gerard Trigga.

09:59.000 --> 10:00.831
G-dog.

10:01.040 --> 10:03.508
Anyone else?

10:03.720 --> 10:06.359
No one?

10:06.560 --> 10:13.193
Well, they are,
or were... atheists.

